    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">738.3915/206: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé des Affaires in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brewer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-01T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Department informed that Haitian Government has advised its Minister Santo
                    Domingo to inform Dominican Government that it is prepared to enter into <hi
                        rend="italic">pourparlers</hi> relative to boundary question. Confer with
                    Military Government and report at once whether Haitian Minister is empowered to
                    discuss this matter on the lines of note from Dominican Foreign Office of
                    December 22 to him proposing arbitration of whole question by the Pope or
                    whether Haitian Minister has been instructed to discuss direct settlement of the
                    boundary dispute.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
